said there was no factual support for the claim that car companies were
selling stocks.
As to palladium catalysts, Allied-Signal followed their initial announcement
in a matter of hours with a follow-up statement saying that although its new
catalyst system would become an important part of its new business, it would
not replace traditional platinum or rhodium based systems.
Impala and Rustenburg's views do not, however, enjoy complete support from
the broking community. One local analyst said that while he would not
discount a certain amount of mischief on the part of customers, he had
limited sympathy for producers complaining that their market was being
disrupted. Arguing that concern about the Japanese economy was the main
reason why PGM prices had cracked, he said local producers would have to
send a signal by closing shafts for the price to recover.
</TEXT>
