<HEADLINE>
FT  05 MAR 93 / International Company News: Pepsi to invest Dollars 750m in
Mexico over five years
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Agencies
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MEXICO CITY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
PEPSICO said it would invest about Dollars 750m over the next five years to
strengthen its bottling operations, extend its distribution network and
market its products more aggressively in Mexico, agencies report from Mexico
City.
'This involves an immediate investment of Dollars 115m in association with
Pepsi's bottlers in Mexico, which will generate important economic benefits
for the country, among them the creation of 10,000 new jobs,' according to a
PepsiCo de Mexico news release issued at a news conference by Pepsi Cola
International president Mr Christopher Sinclair.
Mr Sinclair said Pepsi had bought shares in three Mexican bottling firms to
increase its bottling and distribution capacity, with 29 per cent of Grupo
Embotelladores Unidas, 49 per cent of Grupo Protexa, and 20 per cent of
Grupo Rello.
Pepsi expects to modernise some facilities and will build a new bottling
plant in the Tampico region, he said.
Pepsi Cola has 31 per cent of the Mexican cola drinks market, up from 26 per
cent two years ago.
</TEXT>
