FT  05 MAR 93 / International Capital Markets: Canadian securities industry
sees profit fall
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Canadian securities industry saw operating profits fall 10 per cent to
CDollars 676m in 1992, Reuter reports from Toronto. The Investment Dealers
Association of Canada said total revenues for the Canadian securities
industry rose to CDollars 3.4bn from CDollars 3.1bn. Canadian dealers earned
an average 18 per cent return on shareholders' equity.
Bethlehem Steel has sold 5m shares of Dollars 3.50 cumulative convertible
preferred stock at Dollars 50 per share, Reuter reports. The private
placement was arranged by Salomon Bros and JP Morgan Securities. The shares
are convertible into Bethlehem common stock.
Visa International said its market share in the Dollars 880bn worldwide
market for all purpose cards rose to 52 per cent in 1992 from 51.5 per cent
in 1991, Reuter reports.
Worldwide card sales volume rose by 15.8 per cent to Dollars 457.9bn in
1992, while the number of Visa cards issued rose by 9.5 per cent to more
than Dollars 304.3m.
