<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAR 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Over-supply and over-stocking apply through much of the wool market. In
Australia there is the official stockpile of nearly 4 million bales,
practically a full season's output, which overhangs the market even though
disposals ara currently at a standstill. Resistance to present low prices ,
in real terms the lowest on record, is causing Australian growers to
withdraw their wool and this involves a privately held and financed backlog
which again overhangs the market. Processors in major consumer countries in
Europe and the Far East are often heavily stocked also.
