FT  04 MAR 93 / UK Company News: US agricultural group bids for Greencore
stake
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM COONE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DUBLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Irish government confirmed yesterday that it had received an offer from
Archer Daniels Midland, the US agriculture conglomerate, for its remaining
30.4 per cent stake in Greencore, the Irish sugar and foods company, but
appears to have bowed to political pressure in throwing open the stake to
other offers until March 24.
Greencore's shares resumed trading yesterday, closing at 269p up 24p from
their suspension price.
Mr Joe Walsh, the agriculture minister, said yesterday 'We will have to
await the price which any company is prepared to pay for the shares, and
then (consider) the strategic long-term interest .. We are giving an
opportunity to Irish companies particularly to make a bid for this remaining
stake, because the only interest shown so far is that of ADM'.
He said there has been interest by some Irish companies 'but the only
precise bid' had been made by ADM. 'We have an offer on the table of 260p
per share, but that is a once-off sale, and that is not what the government
is interested in.'
